node.text:
Prepare yourselves... @whatsthomaseating and I challenged each other to a blind taste test of the new @edys @dreyers Rocky Road Collection and honestly, I've never loved my job more!! Take a wild guess who has the better palate.... #ad

If you're down to get crazy and try all the insanely delish flavors, THIS IS YOUR MOMENT. Now through Wednesday, June 9, buy just one full-size flavor from the EDY'S or Dreyer’s recently launched and get the rest of the collection for free when you share a photo of your ice cream on Instagram. Details on how to enter are below! Which flavor would you try first?

🍦 Purchase one of the six Rocky Road Collection flavors at a national grocery retailer near you. Mocha Almond Avenue, Brownie Brick Road, Cookie Cobblestone, Chocolate Peanut Butter Park, Salted Caramel Pretzel Path and/or The Original Rocky Road
🍦 Share a photo of your purchase on Instagram via an in-feed post or Instagram story using the #NationalRockyRoadDay. Can’t make it to the store? No problem! Just comment on @edys or @dreyers promotion post using #NationalRockyRoadDay with one sentence about which flavor of the Rocky Road Collection you’re most excited to try and why.
🍦 Make sure you’re following @edys and @dreyers and tag the handles in your post. Don’t forget to set your profile to Public so they can see your entry!
🍦 EDY'S (Dreyer's) will direct message eligible entrants while supplies last with next steps on how to claim their free ice cream!
NO PURCHASE NECESSARY. Limit to one entry per person. Open to legal residents of the 50 United States (D.C), 13 and older. Entries must be received by 11:59pm PDT on 6/9/21. For Official Rules, go to the link in the @edys @dreyers bio.

node.text: Remember when I woke up at the crack of dawn a few weeks and was in full glam by 3:30am! It was clearly for a good cause because I was then plopped in front of a bunch of cameras to fill everyone in on The United States of Pork!! It was a national survey conducted by The National Pork Board to find the #1 pork dish from around American and surprise surprise California got the carnitas burrito! I turned it into a carnitas burrito bowl and honestly, I’m thriving!! Recipe is linked in my profile and check @nationalporkboard to see the #1 recipe from your state https://whatsgabycooking.com/carnitas-burrito-bowl/

node.text: It’s back to school season and you know what that means… we’re re-living my favorite meal from childhood today! Get ready for Garlic Buttered Angel Hair with Burrata - a family favorite since I was seven years old and the perfect way to get dinner on the table in under 20 mins. Get yourself some @landolakesktchn unsalted butter and an insane amount of garlic then head over to the blog for the recipe!!

node.text: Anyone else feel like they're missing out on some Italian vacations this year? My IG feed has been bombarded with Italian vacations and I have some serious FOMO. We’re not getting over to Italy until next year so for the time being, I’ll just be over here with some of that incredible @VeroGustoSauce trying to make it feel like I’m on some piazza with a slice of Caprese Focaccia Bread and a spritz! This quick and easy focaccia has plenty of cheese, fresh basil and the best Vero Gusto Tomato & Basil sauce to bring it all together! Simple, clean and delish ingredients rolled up into a perfect bite! #VeroGusto Recipe is linked in my bio and HAPPY FRIDAY!! https://whatsgabycooking.com/caprese-focaccia-bread/

node.text: This isn’t just any Three Cheese Pizza… it’s loaded with mozzarella, goat cheese and burrata. It’s the trifecta of cheeses on a pizza plus 2 kinds of pizza sauce. BRING IT ON! node.text:
You knew it had to happen - I had about 4 leftover bags of Tate's Bake Shop cookies from last week and I made the most incredible cookie cake (we used to make these every year for my bff’s birthday in the shape of an E for Emily and honestly nothing is better) #ad
Traditionally we’d make them with wafer cookies - but those days are over. Gimme those Tate’s and some whipped cream and chocolate shavings and GAME OVER. Best to make this beauty the night before you’re serving so all the flavors can meld together.  YOU ARE WELCOME! Linking the recipe in my profile! https://whatsgabycooking.com/cookie-icebox-cake/
